						<summary>

						<p>On a slab planted in front of the Sōmalingēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1049 • • • .</p>						

						<p>States that Guṇḍi-Reḍḍi of Gāralūru and his son Nallapaya died in a battle and went to heaven, after securing victory to for Bētarāja.</p>						

